%% Diagram: GraphQL N+1 vs DataLoader batching within one event-loop tick
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Q as GraphQL Engine
    participant R as Order.user resolver
    participant L as DataLoader (per request)
    participant DB as Database

    Note over Q,DB: Naive N+1 (no DataLoader)
    Q->>R: resolve order 1
    R->>DB: SELECT user WHERE id=1
    DB-->>R: row
    Q->>R: resolve order 2
    R->>DB: SELECT user WHERE id=2
    DB-->>R: row
    Q->>R: resolve order N
    R->>DB: SELECT user WHERE id=N
    DB-->>R: row

    Note over Q,DB: With DataLoader (single tick)
    Q->>R: resolve order 1
    R->>L: load(1)
    Q->>R: resolve order 2
    R->>L: load(2)
    Q->>R: resolve order N
    R->>L: load(N)
    Note over L: end of tick<br/>coalesce keys
    L->>DB: SELECT user WHERE id IN (1,2,...,N)
    DB-->>L: rows in input key order
    L-->>R: resolved promises
